CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 12, 1959, pg. A15, reads: "Final Plans - Eric Springer, member of the local Urban League board, and Mrs. Anne Waters, chairman of the sponsors' committee, with Milo Manly, deputy director of Fair Employment Practices Commission, look over plans for the Holly Ball which will be held Friday, Dec. 18, at Pittsburgh's new Hilton Hotel."
TitMainTitle: Eric Springer, Anne Waters, and Milo Manly meeting to plan Urban League Guild's Holly Ball, possibly at Hilton Hotel
